Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

  • My meme

    My meme

    This is my meme which is a cat with some text on it, related to the emotion of the cat and related to what I feel when I start to study!

    library(magick) 

## Part B: Meme creation

# Create blank image with pink back ground
background <- image_blank(width = 50, height = 250, color = "pink")


# Read image of a cat
cat <- image_read("https://vcahospitals.com/-/media/2/vca/images/lifelearn-images-foldered/10696/unkempt_cat.ashx")


# Add the test on the image
text <- "Feel tired when I study"

meme <- cat %>%
  image_annotate(text, size = 25, color = "white") %>%
  image_annotate("Keep study!", size = 30, color = "pink", location = "+50+100")


# Append the meme to the background
meme <- image_append(c(background, meme, background))


# Save the meme as a new png file
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

  • My animated GIF

    My animated GIF

    This is a GIFT with four very cute cat photos!

    library(magick) 

## Part C. Animated GlF creation

# Load images from URLs
img1 <- image_read("https://pbs.twimg.com/media/BAeuBsnCIAAUITV?format=jpg&name=small")
img2 <- image_read("https://image.petmd.com/files/styles/863x625/public/2021-10/couch-potato-picture-id1219540583.jpg?w=1920&q=75")
img3 <- image_read("https://image.petmd.com/files/styles/863x625/public/Bobcat-Fever-in-domestic-cats-770536417.jpg?w=1920&q=75")
img4 <- image_read("https://image.petmd.com/files/styles/863x625/public/cat-resting.jpg?w=1920&q=75")

# Combine all images and make an animation
animation <- image_join(list(img1, img2, img3, img4))


# Animate the frames with different animation settings
animation <- animation %>%
  image_animate(fps = 2, dispose = "previous") %>%
  image_background("white") %>%
  image_border("gray", "10x10")

# Save the animation as an animated GIF file
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
